<plot>The village of Businitsi in the Trun region is better known for its achievements in the field of ceramics in Japan than it is in Bulgaria. Despite its location many hundreds of kilometers from Salzburg, Vienna, or Prague, there is something distinctly European about it; its two most famous ceramicists are almost exactly like Mozart and Salieri.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?221933</url></doc>
